er:text-velux-button-tertiary-hover aria-disabled:text-velux-button-tertiary-disabled gap-2 md:mt-30 text-velux-black h-8 md:mt-30 text-velux-black h-8" data-variant="link" data-test="comp-link" data-component="CompLink" data-link-type="relative" tabindex="0"><!--[--><!----><span class="" data-test-id="comp-link-text">Discover the benefits of daylight</span><svg class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" data-test="icon-trailing"><!----><use xlink:href="/dist/velux-marketing/client/icon-sprite-bb622257bf7cf195-4de1d8d4.svg#direction-chevron-right-16"></use></svg><!--]--></a></div><!--]--></div></div></div><!--]--></div></section><div class="py-25 old_mobile:py-15 px-10 old_mobile:px-0" placeholder-name="main" language="en-GB" data-v-a74f2494><div class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto"><h2 class="old_mobile:px-6 old_mobile:text-36 old_mobile:leading-[43px] text-48 leading-[57px] font-light mb-16 old_mobile:mb-[37px]">Daylight and Spaces: the journal</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-2 old_mobile:gap-[51px] gap-10 max-w-[1360px] old_mobile:w-full old_mobile:flex old_mobile:flex-col"><a href="/magazine/best-roof-windows-for-home-extensions" class="inline flex flex-col max-w-[660px] old_mobile:max-w-full row-span-3 old_mobile:row-span-1 col-span-1" target><!--[--><div class="aspect-w-4 aspect-h-3 sm:aspect-w-3 sm:aspect-h-2"><div class="w-full h-full object-cover" data-v-0e2b6343><!----></div></div><div class="text-wrapper mt-5 old_tablet:mt-4 old_mobile:mt-5 old_mobile:px-6 mb-7"><span class="mb-4 text-28 font-light leading-[38px] old_mobile:text-28 old_mobile:leading-[33px] old_mobile:font-normal line-clamp-2 m-0">The best roof window solutions for a home extension</span><p class="text-16 font-light leading-[26px] text-old_velux-grey-700 old_mobile:leading-[25px] line-clamp-2">Home extensions can be big or small. No matter the size, a home extension can provide more light and space for your house. Maybe you dream of seeing more of your garden each day. Or perhaps you want a conservatory where you can sit and enjoy the long summer nights. Whatever you may have in mind for your home extension, we have roof windows that can provide you with daylight, ventilation, and ambience.  </p></div><div class="px-0 py-0 mt-7 text-14 leading-115 flex items-center text-old_velux-black font-400 tracking-1 font-w-60 old_mobile:px-6" custom-indent><span class="mr-2">Read the article</span><!----></div><!--]--></a><div class="overflow-hidden" style="margin-left:0;margin-right:0;" data-v-de54d4d5><div class="swiper overflow-visible" style="margin-left:24px;margin-right:24px;" data-v-de54d4d5><!--[--><!--]--><div class="swiper-wrapper"><!--[--><!--]--><!--[--><div class="swiper-slide items-start h-auto" data-v-de54d4d5><!--[--><!--[--><a class="flex mobile:flex-col w-full mobile:h-full max-w-[253px]" href="/magazine/costs-of-replacing-a-window"><div class="max-w-[318px] h-[229px] min-w-[150px] mobile:mb-5 w-full"><div class="w-full h-full object-cover" data-v-0e2b6343><!----></div></div><div class="flex flex-col ml-6 max-w-[318px] mobile:ml-0 mobile:flex-1"><span class="mb-4 old_mobile:mb-4 old_tablet:mb-2 text-22 font-normal leading-[28px] old_mobile:text-20 old_mobile:leading-[24px] line-clamp-4 m-0" data-as-attribute="content">The costs of replacing a roof window - how to budget for your replacement project</span><p class="text-14 font-light leading-19 text-old_velux-grey-700 old_mobile:text-15 old_mobile:font-light old_mobile:leading-[18px] line-clamp-4" data-as-attribute="content">Have you put off replacing your roof windows because it seems like a considerable extra cost? Then read on! Replacing your roof windows is neither as expensive nor as time-consuming as you may think. It all comes down to planning the process and budgeting. Here&#39;s all you need to know about the cost of replacing your roof windows. </p><div class="mt-auto"><div class="px-0 py-0 mt-7 text-14 leading-115 flex items-center text-old_velux-black font-400 tracking-1 font-w-60"><span class="mr-2">Read the article</span><!----></div></div></div></a><!--]--><!--]--><!----></div><div class="swiper-slide items-start h-auto" data-v-de54d4d5><!--[--><!--[--><a class="flex mobile:flex-col w-full mobile:h-full max-w-[253px]" href="/magazine/tips-for-cooling-a-room"><div class="max-w-[318px] h-[229px] min-w-[150px] mobile:mb-5 w-full"><div class="w-full h-full object-cover" data-v-0e2b6343><!----></div></div><div class="flex flex-col ml-6 max-w-[318px] mobile:ml-0 mobile:flex-1"><span class="mb-4 old_mobile:mb-4 old_tablet:mb-2 text-22 font-normal leading-[28px] old_mobile:text-20 old_mobile:leading-[24px] line-clamp-4 m-0" data-as-attribute="content">How to cool down a room: seven strategies to keep your home cool throughout the summer</span><p class="text-14 font-light leading-19 text-old_velux-grey-700 old_mobile:text-15 old_mobile:font-light old_mobile:leading-[18px] line-clamp-4" data-as-attribute="content">The UK climate is changing; data from the Met Office shows that our summers are getting hotter. While you may rejoice in having more time for barbecues and visits to the seaside, no one likes to return home to a hot house. So, follow these seven tips to keep your home cool on even the hottest days, without having fans whirring 24 hours or installing air conditioning. </p><div class="mt-auto"><div class="px-0 py-0 mt-7 text-14 leading-115 flex items-center text-old_velux-black font-400 tracking-1 font-w-60"><span class="mr-2">Read the article</span><!----></div></div></div></a><!--]--><!--]--><!----></div><div class="swiper-slide items-start h-auto" data-v-de54d4d5><!--[--><!--[--><a class="flex mobile:flex-col w-full mobile:h-full max-w-[253px]" href="/magazine/velux-energy-guide"><div class="max-w-[318px] h-[229px] min-w-[150px] mobile:mb-5 w-full"><div class="w-full h-full object-cover" data-v-0e2b6343><!----></div></div><div class="flex flex-col ml-6 max-w-[318px] mobile:ml-0 mobile:flex-1"><span class="mb-4 old_mobile:mb-4 old_tablet:mb-2 text-22 font-normal leading-[28px] old_mobile:text-20 old_mobile:leading-[24px] line-clamp-4 m-0" data-as-attribute="content">The VELUX Energy Guide</span><p class="text-14 font-light leading-19 text-old_velux-grey-700 old_mobile:text-15 old_mobile:font-light old_mobile:leading-[18px] line-clamp-4" data-as-attribute="content">VELUX has a long history of transforming indoor spaces with natural light and fresh air. With a focus on sustainability, improving energy efficiency in our homes remains essential. Roof windows are an effective solution to help reduce energy consumption for heating, cooling, and lighting.</p><div class="mt-auto"><div class="px-0 py-0 mt-7 text-14 leading-115 flex items-center text-old_velux-black font-400 tracking-1 font-w-60"><span class="mr-2">Read the article</span><!----></div></div></div></a><!--]--><!--]--><!----></div><!--]--><!--[--><!--]--></div><!----><!----><div class="swiper-pagination"></div><!--[--><!--[--><div class="flex w-12 h-full translate-y-0 top-0 shadow-none swiper-button left-10 hidden old_mobile:left-0 swiper-button-prev button-prev-cab57c3d-fbd1-496c-8be3-a366903bc68a" style="top:;" data-v-3c712c1e><!----></div><div class="flex w-12 h-full translate-y-0 top-0 shadow-none swiper-button right-10 old_mobile:right-0 swiper-button-next button-next-cab57c3d-fbd1-496c-8be3-a366903bc68a" style="top:;" data-v-3c712c1e><!----></div><!--]--><!--]--></div><!----></div></div></div></div><section id="46cb26e8-7c47-4115-ae72-d4a56d0d551c" data-section-name="headerblockvds-5" class="" placeholder-name="main" language="en-GB" data-v-a74f2494><div class="p-10 vlx-container vlx-grid gap-6"><!----><div class="vlx-grid gap-10 col-span-full"><span class="col-span-full md:col-span-10"><h2 class="vds-font-headline-m word-break" data-heading-size="m" data-heading-bold="false" data-test="text">How can we help you?</h2></span><!----></div></div></section><section id="f61797f9-a715-4b27-a1aa-61cc7f69f892" data-section-name="quicklinksblockvds-6" cla